+# Phase 01 Plan: Local-First Core & Privacy Guardrails
+
+## Objective
+Enforce local-first processing as the default invariant, block remote inference unless explicit project-scoped opt-in exists, and provide auditable/visible trust signals and data-minimized storage behavior.
+
+## Context
+- `.planning/phases/01-local-first-core-privacy-guardrails/01-CONTEXT.md`
+- `.planning/phases/01-local-first-core-privacy-guardrails/01-RESEARCH.md`
+- `.planning/REQUIREMENTS.md`
+
+<tasks>
+  <task id="P01-T01" wave="1" type="auto">
+    <title>Implement central privacy guard, project-scoped consent state, and secure remote transport</title>
+    <requirements>PRIV-01,PRIV-02</requirements>
+    <depends_on></depends_on>
+    <files>
+      <file>src/lib/types/privacy.ts</file>
+      <file>src/lib/privacy/policy.ts</file>
+      <file>src/lib/privacy/consent-store.ts</file>
+      <file>src/lib/privacy/guard.ts</file>
+      <file>src/lib/privacy/transport.ts</file>
+      <file>src/app/api/privacy/consent/route.ts</file>
+      <file>tests/privacy/privacy-guard.test.ts</file>
+      <file>tests/privacy/transport.test.ts</file>
+    </files>
+    <action>Create one non-bypassable privacy gateway used for inference/embedding entry points. Default mode must be LOCAL_ONLY; remote path may resolve only when local confidence is below configured threshold and project/workspace consent is explicitly true. Implement consent read/write/revoke APIs scoped by projectId (not global and not per-request). Build remote transport through a single client factory that enforces HTTPS-only and certificate validation, and rejects insecure endpoint configs. Do not allow direct remote calls outside guard.ts.</action>
+    <verify>
+      <automated>npm run lint &amp;&amp; npm run test -- tests/privacy/privacy-guard.test.ts tests/privacy/transport.test.ts</automated>
+      <manual>Call consent API for one project to opt in and revoke; verify guard decisions change only for that project and insecure http:// endpoint is rejected.</manual>
+      <sampling_rate>run after this task commits, before wave 2 begins</sampling_rate>
+    </verify>
+    <done>Local-first decision engine exists and is wired as the sole entry path; remote inference cannot execute without project-scoped opt-in and secure transport constraints.</done>
+  </task>
+
+  <task id="P01-T02" wave="2" type="auto">
+    <title>Add Privacy Center, inline remote-use badges, and filterable audit log surface</title>
+    <requirements>PRIV-02</requirements>
+    <depends_on>P01-T01</depends_on>
+    <files>
+      <file>src/lib/privacy/audit-log.ts</file>
+      <file>src/app/api/privacy/events/route.ts</file>
+      <file>src/app/api/privacy/settings/route.ts</file>
+      <file>src/components/privacy/PrivacyCenter.tsx</file>
+      <file>src/components/common/InferenceBadge.tsx</file>
+      <file>src/lib/hooks/usePrivacy.ts</file>
+      <file>src/app/settings/privacy/page.tsx</file>
+      <file>src/app/page.tsx</file>
+      <file>tests/privacy/privacy-guard.test.ts</file>
+    </files>
+    <action>Implement dedicated Privacy Center UI with project-scoped opt-in toggle and one-click revoke action. Add inline inference badges to generated response surfaces that show remote/local mode and short reason when remote path was used. Persist remote inference events in a filterable audit log (project, mode, reason, connector, time range) and expose retrieval API for Privacy Center. Ensure every remote event includes timestamp and decision reason from guard output.</action>
+    <verify>
+      <automated>npm run lint &amp;&amp; npm run test -- tests/privacy/privacy-guard.test.ts</automated>
+      <manual>In UI, opt in one project, trigger a low-confidence flow, verify response shows remote badge + reason and event appears in Privacy Center audit log; revoke and confirm subsequent responses stay local-only.</manual>
+      <sampling_rate>run after this task commits</sampling_rate>
