+      <file>src/app/page.tsx</file>
+      <file>tests/privacy/privacy-guard.test.ts</file>
+    </files>
+    <action>Implement dedicated Privacy Center UI with project-scoped opt-in toggle and one-click revoke action. Add inline inference badges to generated response surfaces that show remote/local mode and short reason when remote path was used. Persist remote inference events in a filterable audit log (project, mode, reason, connector, time range) and expose retrieval API for Privacy Center. Implement explicit deny-path behavior from locked decision: when remote inference is denied (user consent absent/revoked), return local-only output plus a user-visible note that remote inference could improve output quality.</action>
+    <verify>
+      <automated>npm run lint &amp;&amp; npm run test -- tests/privacy/privacy-guard.test.ts</automated>
+      <manual>In UI, deny remote for one project and trigger a low-confidence flow; verify response stays local-only and shows a note that remote could improve output. Then opt in and verify response shows remote badge + reason and event appears in Privacy Center audit log.</manual>
+      <sampling_rate>run after this task commits</sampling_rate>
+    </verify>
+    <done>Users can view/change project-scoped remote consent, inspect remote-use events, and always see explicit local-only deny messaging or remote-use badge/reason in responses.</done>
+  </task>
+</tasks>
