+# Stack Research
+
+**Domain:** Numbered CLI selection UX for AI-assisted workflows
+**Researched:** 2026-02-24
+**Confidence:** HIGH
+
+## Recommended Stack
+
+### Core Technologies
+
+| Technology | Version | Purpose | Why Recommended |
+|------------|---------|---------|-----------------|
+| Node.js | 20.x | Runtime for CLI helpers and prompts | Matches existing Codex scripts; broad ecosystem; stable LTS |
+| Built-in `readline` | N/A | Console input handling without heavy deps | Zero-dependency, works in sandboxed shells |
+| `fs` + `JSON` | N/A | Persist lightweight selection context if needed | Already available; avoids new formats |
+
+### Supporting Libraries
+
+| Library | Version | Purpose | When to Use |
+|---------|---------|---------|-------------|
+| `colorette` | 2.x | Colorize numbers vs text for quick scanning | Optional: when terminals support ANSI and UX needs emphasis |
+| `strip-ansi` | 7.x | Sanitize AI text before parsing numbers | When AI output may include color/markdown artifacts |
+| `zod` or `valibot` | 3.x / 1.x | Validate structured AI responses (arrays of strings/objects) | When normalizing AI outputs beyond plain text lists |
+
+### Development Tools
+
+| Tool | Purpose | Notes |
+|------|---------|-------|
+| `node --test` | Quick unit checks for parser/selector | Ships with Node 20; no extra deps |
+| `eslint` (optional) | Guard against unhandled promises/console parsing bugs | Only if linting already present; otherwise skip to stay lean |
+
+## Installation
+
+```bash
+# Optional UX dependencies
+npm install colorette@2 strip-ansi@7
+
+# Optional validation
+npm install zod@3
+```
+
+## Alternatives Considered
+
+| Recommended | Alternative | When to Use Alternative |
+|-------------|-------------|-------------------------|
+| `readline` | `inquirer` | Use only if you need multi-select/search; heavier and adds prompts we do not need |
+| `colorette` | `chalk` | Chalk is fine but larger; colorette is ESM/CJS friendly and tiny |
+| Plain strings | `table`/`cliui` renderers | Use tables only when options need columns; for numbered lists plain lines are clearer |
+
+## What NOT to Use
+
+| Avoid | Why | Use Instead |
+|-------|-----|-------------|
+| Free-form AI HTML/markdown rendering | Harder to parse consistently; brittle across terminals | Enforce plain numbered text schema |
+| Interactive TUI frameworks (blessed/ink) | Overkill for simple selection; brittle in headless runs | Stick to readline + color-only styling |
+
+## Stack Patterns by Variant
+
+**If running in non-interactive/sandboxed shells:**
+- Accept preselected number via env/flag; skip readline.
+- Log numbered options for audit.
+
+**If output comes from AI with metadata (JSON array):**
+- Parse JSON first; fall back to regex numbered lines.
+- Validate structure with zod/valibot before rendering.
+
+## Version Compatibility
+
+| Package A | Compatible With | Notes |
+|-----------|-----------------|-------|
+| colorette@2 | Node 20 | Works in CJS; lightweight |
+| strip-ansi@7 | Node 14+ | Safe for cleaning AI outputs |
+
+## Sources
+
+- Prior CLI selector patterns from Copilot CLI/Aider (observed behaviors)
+- Node.js readline, colorette, strip-ansi docs (checked for compatibility)
