"src/lib/sync/engine.ts\"\n      to: \"src/lib/sync/health.ts\"\n      via: \"provider errors are normalized to connector health state transitions\"\n      pattern: \"health classifier\"\n---\n\n# Phase 02-01 Plan: Connector Runtime Foundation and Resumable Sync Core\n\n## Objective\nEstablish the shared connector runtime contract, resumable incremental sync engine, and health/progress state model used by all Phase 2 provider integrations.\n\n## Context\n- `.planning/phases/02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync/02-CONTEXT.md`\n- `.planning/phases/02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync/02-RESEARCH.md`\n- `.planning/REQUIREMENTS.md`\n\n<tasks>\n  <task id=\"P02-01-T01\" wave=\"1\" type=\"auto\">\n    <name>Define connector, cursor, and health contracts with persistent store support</name>\n    <title>Define connector, cursor, and health contracts with persistent store support</title>\n    <requirements>INTG-03,INTG-04,PERF-02</requirements>\n    <depends_on></depends_on>\n    <files>\n      <file>src/lib/types/connectors.ts</file>\n      <file>src/lib/connectors/store.ts</file>\n      <file>src/lib/sync/checkpoints.ts</file>\n      <file>src/lib/sync/health.ts</file>\n      <file>tests/connectors/sync-engine.test.ts</file>\n    </files>\n    <action>Create typed connector contracts covering provider identity, source scope, cursor payload, progress counters, and the locked health state model. Implement persistent connector state + checkpoint helpers with per-connector and per-source keys so resume never depends on in-memory state. Add health classifier utilities that map 429 to `rate_limited`, 401/403 to `auth_expired`, and apply required status priority ordering (`auth_expired` &gt; `error` &gt; `rate_limited` &gt; `syncing` &gt; `connected`).</action>\n    <verify>\n      <automated>npm run lint &amp;&amp; npm run test -- tests/connectors/sync-engine.test.ts</automated>\n      <manual>Inspect persisted connector records to confirm separate checkpoints exist for each source (for example Slack channel A vs channel B) and that status priority sorting places auth_expired above rate_limited.</manual>\n      <sampling_rate>run after this task commits</sampling_rate>\n    </verify>\n    <done>Connector runtime primitives exist and enforce source-aware checkpoints plus the required health state semantics.\n</done>\n  </task>\n\n  <task id=\"P02-01-T02\" wave=\"1\" type=\"auto\">\n    <name>Implement shared incremental engine and sync-now endpoint with checkpoint-after-persist semantics</name>\n    <title>Implement shared incremental engine and sync-now endpoint with checkpoint-after-persist semantics</title>\n    <requirements>INTG-03,PERF-02</requirements>\n    <depends_on>P02-01-T01</depends_on>\n    <files>\n      <file>src/lib/sync/engine.ts</file>\n      <file>src/app/api/connectors/route.ts</file>\n      <file>src/app/api/connectors/[id]/sync/route.ts</file>\n      <file>tests/connectors/sync-engine.test.ts</file>\n    </files>\n    <action>Build a reusable incremental sync runner that accepts adapter callbacks, loads last checkpoint, processes changed records, upserts idempotently, and writes next checkpoint only after successful persistence. Emit progress snapshots with per-source counters (`scanned`, `changed`, `upserted`), current stage, throughput, and retry metadata. Expose API routes for connector listing/config fetch and manual `Sync now` invocation that use this engine (not connector-specific one-offs).</action>\n    <verify>\n      <automated>npm run lint &amp;&amp; npm run test -- tests/connectors/sync-engine.test.ts</automated>\n      <manual>Trigger sync-now, interrupt process mid-run, and restart; confirm resumed run continues from saved checkpoint and does not duplicate previously upserted records.</manual>\n      <sampling_rate>run after this task commits</sampling_rate>\n    </verify>\n    <done>Incremental sync is resumable by design, exposes progress telemetry, and is reachable through shared connector APIs.\n</done>\n  </task>\n</tasks>\n\n## Verification Criteria\n- Checkpoint updates occur only after successful record persistence.\n- Health state classification and priority logic match locked context semantics.\n- Sync-now API executes shared engine and exposes progress counters for UI consumption.\n\n## Must Haves\n<must_haves>\n  <must_have id=\"MH-01\" requirement=\"INTG-03\">Incremental runs process only changed/new records and safely resume from persisted per-source checkpoints.</must_have>\n  <must_have id=\"MH-02\" requirement=\"INTG-04\">Connector health state transitions are normalized and include required statuses with correct priority routing.</must_have>\n  <must_have id=\"MH-03\" requirement=\"PERF-02\">Sync progress snapshots provide persistent, restart-safe visibility into current step and per-source counters.</must_have>\n</must_haves>\nEOF\n\ncat > .planning/phases/02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync/02-02-PLAN.md <<'EOF'\n---\nphase: 02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync\nplan: 02\ntype: execute\nwave: 2\ndepends_on: [02-01]\nrequirements: [INTG-01, INTG-03]\nfiles_modified:\n  - src/lib/connectors/slack.ts\n  - src/app/api/connectors/slack/oauth/route.ts\n  - src/app/api/connectors/slack/channels/route.ts\n  - src/app/api/connectors/slack/sync/route.ts\n  - src/components/connectors/SlackConnectorCard.tsx\n  - src/lib/hooks/useConnectorStatus.ts\n  - tests/connectors/slack-adapter.test.ts\nautonomous: true\nmust_haves:\n  truths:\n    - \"User can connect exactly one Slack workspace and choose channels included in sync scope.\"\n    - \"Slack incremental sync only ingests net-new/changed records after first import window.\"\n    - \"Slack connector surfaces rate limit/auth-expired/error state transitions through shared health model.\"\n  artifacts:\n    - path: \"src/lib/connectors/slack.ts\"\n      provides: \"Slack adapter implementing OAuth token usage, channel discovery, and incremental history sync.\"\n    - path: \"src/app/api/connectors/slack/channels/route.ts\"\n      provides: \"Channel selection read/write endpoint used to scope initial and incremental sync.\"\n    - path: \"src/components/connectors/SlackConnectorCard.tsx\"\n      provides: \"UI flow for connect, channel selection, and manual sync-now trigger.\"\n  key_links:\n    - from: \"src/app/api/connectors/slack/sync/route.ts\"\n      to: \"src/lib/sync/engine.ts\"\n      via: \"Slack sync route delegates execution to shared incremental engine\"\n      pattern: \"engine delegation\"\n    - from: \"src/components/connectors/SlackConnectorCard.tsx\"\n      to: \"src/app/api/connectors/slack/channels/route.ts\"\n      via: \"selected channels are saved and used as source scope\"\n      pattern: \"channel scope persistence\"\n---\n\n# Phase 02-02 Plan: Slack Connectivity and Channel-Scoped Incremental Ingestion\n\n## Objective\nDeliver one-workspace Slack connectivity with channel selection and incremental, resumable ingestion through the shared sync core.\n\n## Context\n- `.planning/phases/02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync/02-CONTEXT.md`\n- `.planning/phases/02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync/02-RESEARCH.md`\n- `.planning/phases/02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync/02-01-PLAN.md`\n\n<tasks>\n  <task id=\"P02-02-T01\" wave=\"2\" type=\"auto\">\n    <name>Implement Slack adapter, OAuth/connect routes, and channel-scope persistence</name>\n    <title>Implement Slack adapter, OAuth/connect routes, and channel-scope persistence</title>\n    <requirements>INTG-01,INTG-03</requirements>\n    <depends_on>P02-01-T01,P02-01-T02</depends_on>\n    <files>\n      <file>src/lib/connectors/slack.ts</file>\n      <file>src/app/api/connectors/slack/oauth/route.ts</file>\n      <file>src/app/api/connectors/slack/channels/route.ts</file>\n      <file>src/app/api/connectors/slack/sync/route.ts</file>\n      <file>tests/connectors/slack-adapter.test.ts</file>\n    </files>\n    <action>Implement Slack connector integration for one workspace: OAuth token exchange/storage, channel discovery, and selected-channel scope persistence. Enforce first-sync window selection (default to a controlled window such as 30 days) before first import. Use Slack cursor/timestamp semantics for incremental runs and route all ingestion through the shared sync engine so checkpoint-after-persist and idempotent upsert rules are inherited.</action>\n    <verify>\n      <automated>npm run lint &amp;&amp; npm run test -- tests/connectors/slack-adapter.test.ts tests/connectors/sync-engine.test.ts</automated>\n      <manual>Connect one Slack workspace, select two channels, run first sync with 30-day window, then rerun sync and confirm only changed/new messages are ingested.</manual>\n      <sampling_rate>run after this task commits</sampling_rate>\n    </verify>\n    <done>Slack connector supports workspace connect + channel selection and executes source-aware incremental sync behavior without full replay.\n</done>\n  </task>\n\n  <task id=\"P02-02-T02\" wave=\"2\" type=\"auto\">\n    <name>Add Slack connector card UX for connect state, channel scope, and sync-now control</name>\n    <title>Add Slack connector card UX for connect state, channel scope, and sync-now control</title>\n    <requirements>INTG-01</requirements>\n    <depends_on>P02-02-T01</depends_on>\n    <files>\n      <file>src/components/connectors/SlackConnectorCard.tsx</file>\n      <file>src/lib/hooks/useConnectorStatus.ts</file>\n      <file>src/app/settings/connectors/page.tsx</file>\n    </files>\n    <action>Create Slack connector card UI that shows workspace connection status, channel selection controls, last sync timestamp, and manual `Sync now` trigger. The UI must surface state transitions from shared health semantics and show actionable error text for `rate_limited` and `auth_expired` without inventing new status names.</action>\n    <verify>\n      <automated>npm run lint</automated>\n      <manual>From connectors settings page: connect Slack, select channels