ter interface and config validation.\"\n    - path: \"src/lib/connectors/tracker-github.ts\"\n      provides: \"GitHub Issues incremental adapter using update-time cursor semantics.\"\n    - path: \"src/lib/connectors/tracker-linear.ts\"\n      provides: \"Linear incremental adapter using GraphQL pagination filtered by updatedAt.\"\n    - path: \"src/components/connectors/TrackerConnectorCard.tsx\"\n      provides: \"UI flow for provider choice, connect state, and sync status/actions.\"\n  key_links:\n    - from: \"src/app/api/connectors/tracker/sync/route.ts\"\n      to: \"src/lib/sync/engine.ts\"\n      via: \"tracker sync routes execute through shared incremental runner\"\n      pattern: \"engine delegation\"\n    - from: \"src/components/connectors/TrackerConnectorCard.tsx\"\n      to: \"src/app/api/connectors/tracker/route.ts\"\n      via: \"provider connect config drives tracker adapter selection\"\n      pattern: \"provider-specific configuration\"\n---\n\n# Phase 02-03 Plan: Tracker Connectivity (GitHub/Linear) and Incremental Metadata Sync\n\n## Objective\nDeliver one-tracker connectivity (GitHub Issues or Linear) with metadata ingestion and changed-record incremental behavior aligned with resumable sync guarantees.\n\n## Context\n- `.planning/phases/02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync/02-CONTEXT.md`\n- `.planning/phases/02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync/02-RESEARCH.md`\n- `.planning/phases/02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync/02-01-PLAN.md`\n\n<tasks>\n  <task id=\"P02-03-T01\" wave=\"2\" type=\"auto\">\n    <name>Implement tracker adapter layer and provider-specific incremental sync for GitHub and Linear</name>\n    <title>Implement tracker adapter layer and provider-specific incremental sync for GitHub and Linear</title>\n    <requirements>INTG-02,INTG-03</requirements>\n    <depends_on>P02-01-T01,P02-01-T02</depends_on>\n    <files>\n      <file>src/lib/connectors/tracker.ts</file>\n      <file>src/lib/connectors/tracker-github.ts</file>\n      <file>src/lib/connectors/tracker-linear.ts</file>\n      <file>src/app/api/connectors/tracker/sync/route.ts</file>\n      <file>tests/connectors/tracker-adapter.test.ts</file>\n    </files>\n    <action>Create tracker adapter abstraction with two concrete implementations: GitHub Issues and Linear. For GitHub, use update-time incremental filters (not creation-time only) so edits and reopen/close transitions are captured. For Linear, use paginated GraphQL queries filtered by `updatedAt` checkpoint. Both adapters must emit normalized change records and consume the shared checkpoint + health classifier utilities.\n</action>\n    <verify>\n      <automated>npm run lint &amp;&amp; npm run test -- tests/connectors/tracker-adapter.test.ts tests/connectors/sync-engine.test.ts</automated>\n      <manual>Connect tracker provider, run initial sync, modify an existing issue, rerun sync, and confirm modified issue is re-ingested as changed (not skipped).</manual>\n      <sampling_rate>run after this task commits</sampling_rate>\n    </verify>\n    <done>Tracker connector supports one configured provider and captures both new and changed issue metadata incrementally.</done>\n  </task>\n\n  <task id=\"P02-03-T02\" wave=\"2\" type=\"auto\">\n    <name>Add tracker connector API and UI for provider selection, connect state, and sync control</name>\n    <title>Add tracker connector API and UI for provider selection, connect state, and sync control</title>\n    <requirements>INTG-02</requirements>\n    <depends_on>P02-03-T01</depends_on>\n    <files>\n      <file>src/app/api/connectors/tracker/route.ts</file>\n      <file>src/components/connectors/TrackerConnectorCard.tsx</file>\n      <file>src/app/settings/connectors/page.tsx</file>\n    </files>\n    <action>Implement tracker connector configuration APIs and card UI to choose provider (GitHub Issues or Linear), save credentials/config, and trigger manual sync. UI must render normalized health states and explicit re-auth action for `auth_expired`, without collapsing states into generic error labels.</action>\n    <verify>\n      <automated>npm run lint</automated>\n      <manual>On connectors page, configure GitHub or Linear, trigger sync-now, then simulate token expiry and confirm auth_expired state shows reconnect CTA and preserves last successful sync timestamp.</manual>\n      <sampling_rate>run after this task commits</sampling_rate>\n    </verify>\n    <done>User can connect one tracker source, run syncs, and act on provider-specific auth/health outcomes through unified state semantics.</done>\n  </task>\n</tasks>\n\n## Verification Criteria\n- Tracker provider can be configured as GitHub or Linear with one active connection.\n- Incremental runs reprocess changed issues/metadata updates, not just newly created records.\n- Health/error handling produces actionable auth-expired and rate-limit states.\n\n## Must Haves\n<must_haves>\n  <must_have id=\"MH-06\" requirement=\"INTG-02\">User can connect one project tracker (GitHub Issues or Linear) and ingest issue metadata.</must_have>\n  <must_have id=\"MH-07\" requirement=\"INTG-03\">Tracker incremental sync captures net-new and changed records after first import.</must_have>\n</must_haves>\nEOF\n\ncat > .planning/phases/02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync/02-04-PLAN.md <<'EOF'\n---\nphase: 02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync\nplan: 04\ntype: execute\nwave: 3\ndepends_on: [02-02, 02-03]\nrequirements: [INTG-04, PERF-02, INTG-03]\nfiles_modified:\n  - src/app/settings/connectors/page.tsx\n  - src/components/connectors/SyncDashboard.tsx\n  - src/components/layout/HeaderSyncStatus.tsx\n  - src/components/common/SyncToast.tsx\n  - src/lib/hooks/useSyncStatus.ts\n  - src/app/api/connectors/health/route.ts\n  - tests/connectors/sync-status.test.tsx\nautonomous: true\nmust_haves:\n  truths:\n    - \"Sync status is visible in both dedicated dashboard and always-visible compact indicator.\"\n    - \"Progress visibility includes per-connector counters and current step, not percent-only reporting.\"\n    - \"Interrupted sync resumes with preserved progress/checkpoint context and exposes actionable recovery controls.\"\n    - \"Connector health states and priority ordering remain consistent across backend and UI surfaces.\"\n  artifacts:\n    - path: \"src/components/connectors/SyncDashboard.tsx\"\n      provides: \"Detailed sync and health dashboard with counters, throughput, and recovery controls.\"\n    - path: \"src/components/layout/HeaderSyncStatus.tsx\"\n      provides: \"Compact always-visible status indicator with traffic-light semantics.\"\n    - path: \"src/app/api/connectors/health/route.ts\"\n      provides: \"Aggregated health/progress endpoint consumed by dashboard and compact indicator.\"\n    - path: \"src/components/common/SyncToast.tsx\"\n      provides: \"Transient completion/failure notifications paired with persistent status cards.\"\n  key_links:\n    - from: \"src/lib/hooks/useSyncStatus.ts\"\n      to: \"src/app/api/connectors/health/route.ts\"\n      via: \"polling/subscription hook feeds both dashboard and compact indicator\"\n      pattern: \"shared status data source\"\n    - from: \"src/components/connectors/SyncDashboard.tsx\"\n      to: \"src/app/api/connectors/[id]/sync/route.ts\"\n      via: \"recovery controls call sync-now and reconnect flows\"\n      pattern: \"actionable recovery controls\"\n---\n\n# Phase 02-04 Plan: Dual-Surface Sync Visibility, Health UX, and Recovery Controls\n\n## Objective\nShip the required sync visibility surfaces (dashboard + compact indicator), health status semantics, and interruption recovery UX for Phase 2 completion.\n\n## Context\n- `.planning/phases/02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync/02-CONTEXT.md`\n- `.planning/phases/02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync/02-RESEARCH.md`\n- `.planning/phases/02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync/02-02-PLAN.md`\n- `.planning/phases/02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync/02-03-PLAN.md`\n\n<tasks>\n  <task id=\"P02-04-T01\" wave=\"3\" type=\"auto\">\n    <name>Build sync dashboard and compact status indicator powered by a shared health/progress API</name>\n    <title>Build sync dashboard and compact status indicator powered by a shared health/progress API</title>\n    <requirements>INTG-04,PERF-02</requirements>\n    <depends_on>P02-02-T02,P02-03-T02</depends_on>\n    <files>\n      <file>src/app/settings/connectors/page.tsx</file>\n      <file>src/components/connectors/SyncDashboard.tsx</file>\n      <file>src/components/layout/HeaderSyncStatus.tsx</file>\n      <file>src/lib/hooks/useSyncStatus.ts</file>\n      <file>src/app/api/connectors/health/route.ts</file>\n      <file>tests/connectors/sync-status.test.tsx</file>\n    </files>\n    <action>Implement a dedicated sync dashboard and compact always-visible header indicator that both consume one normalized status endpoint. Surface per-connector and per-source counters, current stage, throughput, retry/backoff info, and last-successful-sync timestamps. Preserve locked health semantics and status priority ordering across both surfaces (`auth_expired` &gt; `error` &gt; `rate_limited` &gt; `syncing` &gt; `connected`) with traffic-light glanceability in compact mode.</action>\n    <verify>\n      <automated>npm run lint &amp;&amp; npm run test -- tests/connectors/sync-status.test.tsx</automated>\n      <manual>Start sync and observe dashboard + header indicator update together; confirm counters and stage change over time and status priority rendering is consistent when multiple error states are present.</manual>\n      <sampling_rate>run after this task commits</sampling_rate>\n    </verify>\n    <done>Both required visibility surfaces exist, share one truth source, and expose meaningful progress/health details beyond percent bars.\n</done>\n  </task>\n\n  <task id=\"P02-04-T02\" wave=\"3\" type=\"auto\">\n    <name>Add persistent recovery cards and transient toasts for completion/failure and resume actions</name>\n    <title>Add persistent recovery cards and transient toasts for completion/failure and resume actions</title>\n    <requirements>PERF-02,INTG-03,INTG-04</requirements>\n    <depends_on>P02-04-T01</depends_on>\n    <files>\n      <file>src/components/connectors/SyncDashboard.tsx</file>\n      <file>src/components/common/SyncToast.tsx</file>\n      <file>src/lib/hooks/useSyncStatus.ts</file>\n      <file>tests/connectors/sync-status.test.tsx</file>\n    </files>\n    <action>Implement transient notifications for sync completion/failure plus persistent status cards containing actionable controls (`Retry`, `Reconnect`, `Resume now`). When sync is interrupted, cards must preserve last checkpoint metadata and explain resume behavior to user confidence. Ensure auth-expired states hard-stop sync and present explicit re-auth CTA while retaining last successful sync context.</action>\n    <verify>\n      <automated>npm run lint &amp;&amp; npm run test -- tests/connectors/sync-status.test.tsx</automated>\n      <manual>Interrupt an in-progress sync and verify persistent card offers resume/retry with last checkpoint info; simulate auth expiry and confirm re-auth CTA appears with sync blocked until reconnect.</manual>\n      <sampling_rate>run after this task commits</sampling_rate>\n    </verify>\n    <done>Users receive immediate plus persistent sync outcome feedback and can recover from interruption/auth/rate-limit states without hidden system behavior.</done>\n  </task>\n</tasks>\n\n## Verification Criteria\n- Dashboard and compact indicator are both present and always reflect the same status source.\n- Progress includes counters + stage + throughput, not percent-only abstraction.\n- Interruption and auth-expired scenarios provide clear, actionable recovery paths with preserved sync context.\n\n## Must Haves\n<must_haves>\n  <must_have id=\"MH-08\" requirement=\"INTG-04\">Connector health statuses are visible and action-oriented across product surfaces.</must_have>\n  <must_have id=\"MH-09\" requirement=\"PERF-02\">Initial and subsequent sync runs show progress and resume correctly after interruption.</must_have>\n  <must_have id=\"MH-10\" requirement=\"INTG-03\">Recovery flows keep cursor/checkpoint semantics intact to avoid duplicate or skipped records.</must_have>\n</must_haves>\nEOF\n\ncat > .planning/phases/02-source-connectivity-incremental-sync/PLAN.md <<'EOF'\n# Phase 02 Plan Index: Source Connectivity & Incremental Sync\n\nThis phase is split into four executable plans for reliable connector delivery with resumable sync and UI health visibility:\n\n- `02-01-PLAN.md` (Wave 1): connector runtime contracts, checkpoints, health classification, and shared sync engine.\n- `02-02-PLAN.md` (Wave 2): Slack workspace connect, channel scope, and incremental sync integration.\n- `02-03-PLAN.md` (Wave 2): tracker connect (GitHub/Linear) and incremental issue metadata sync.\n- `02-04-PLAN.md` (Wave 3): sync dashboard + compact indicator, progress telemetry, and recovery UX.\n\n## Wave Structure\n\n- Wave 1: `02-01-PLAN.md`\n- Wave 2: `02-02-PLAN.md`, `02-03-PLAN.md` (both depend on Wave 1)\n- Wave 3: `02-04-PLAN.md` (depends on Wave 2 connector surfaces)\n\n## Requirements Coverage\n\n- `INTG-01`: `02-02-PLAN.md`\n- `INTG-02`: `02-03-PLAN.md`\n- `INTG-03`: `02-01-PLAN.md`, `02-02-PLAN.md`, `02-03-PLAN.md`, `02-04-PLAN.md`\n- `INTG-04`: `02-01-PLAN.md`, `02-04-PLAN.md`\n- `PERF-02`: `02-01-PLAN.md`, `02-04-PLAN.md`\nEOF"} thread_id=019c8fdf-aae9-7903-8070-d5e294976d2a
